Yesterday I was asked to create a user account and use a known vuln bounty platform (BBP) to report a vuln in a 3rd party vendor. Today the BBP tells me that they don't have the hardware to test the reported vuln and asked for more details, tools, etc. (thread... )
vulns that can't be easily triaged shouldn't be handled by BBP as they give extra work for researchers and make them to lose time while the 3rd party vendor continue being vulnerable ...

vendors should understand that outsourcing this for vulns other than on external web apps and public available software is not a good idea and shows how immature in cyber security the vendor is. This is a very bad practice that show how little a vendor cares about security.

this is a good example of how some vendors try to outsource with BBP all the vuln reporting and triage process that results in a bad experience for the researcher and not accomplishing the end goal as the vendor can't (or don't want to) provide hardware and code to the BBP ...

Why I've to create an account in a bugbounty platform for reporting a vulnerability affecting a 3rd party vendor? I just need an easy way to report not wasting time and not following specific procedures "Law 3: Your rules and procedures are not important" https://t.co/Q3jbANLYGx

So, companies shouldn't request researchers to follow specific procedures and do extra steps, they just need tp provide an email to get the report, then they could use their time to do their job and follow any procedure and complete the information the best way they like it
